                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a3/1670: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Edge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-17T15:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 17, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 17—11:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>896. This Embassy’s 836 of December 3, noon.<note n="43" xml:id="d321fn43">Not
                        printed.</note> No reply has been made to the Italian Government’s
                    proposals, it is understood here; but the Chief of the Intelligence Office of
                    the General Staff of the Ministry of Marine, Captain Fernet, has informed the
                    Naval Attaché of this Embassy that it is the opinion of the Ministry of Marine
                    that the proposals are completely unacceptable to the French Government.
                    Information repeated to Rome, Brussels, and London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edge</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
